<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1103,1343]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,304,1103,1128]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Distribution.</emphasis>
Most of Europe (north to south 
<collectingCountry box="[697,790,1103,1127]" name="Sweden" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Sweden</collectingCountry>
), present in southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1047,1144,1103,1127]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">England</collectingCountry>
; rare in southern Europe (confirmed only in Pelopponnese), absent from North Africa (
<bibRefCitation author="Warncke" box="[845,1012,1140,1164]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Warncke, K. (1992) Die Westpalaarktischen Arten der Bienengattung Sphecodes Latr. (Hymenoptera, Apidae, Halictinae). Bericht der Naturforschenden Gesellschaft Augsburg, 52, 9 - 64." type="journal article" year="1992">
Warncke 
<number box="[952,1012,1140,1164]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1103,1343]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,297,1175,1200]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Biology.</emphasis>
Common species especially of warmer and sandy sites. 
<bibRefCitation author="Westrich" box="[959,1143,1175,1199]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Westrich, P. (1989) Die Wildbienen Baden-Wurttembergs. Band. 1 und 2. Eugen Ulmer Verlag, Stuttgart, 972 pp." type="book" year="1989">
Westrich (
<number box="[1077,1135,1175,1199]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1989.0">1989</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
mentioned 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidiusculum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Lasioglossum nitidiusculum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as confirmed host and 
<taxonomicName box="[597,832,1212,1236]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="morio">
<emphasis box="[597,832,1212,1236]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Lasioglossum morio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as likely host, 
<bibRefCitation author="Vegter" box="[1027,1189,1212,1237]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Vegter, K. (1993) Gastheren van enige soorten Sphecodes in Drenthe (Hymenoptera: Apidae). [Hosts of some Sphecodes in Drenthe]. Entomologische Berichten (Amsterdam), 53, 67 - 70. (in Dutch)." type="journal article" year="1993">
Vegter (
<number box="[1122,1180,1212,1236]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1993.0">1993</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName box="[1202,1381,1213,1236]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sexstrigatum">
<emphasis box="[1202,1381,1213,1236]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">L. sexstrigatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Bogusch" box="[151,330,1247,1271]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Bogusch, P. (2003) Biologie vybranych druh u kleptoparazitickych v c el (Hymenoptera: Apocrita, Apoidea). [Biology of selected cuckoo bee species (Hymenoptera: Apocrita, Apoidea)]. Charles University in Prague, Faculty of Sciences, MSc. thesis, unpublished, 111 pp. (in Czech)." type="book" year="2003">
Bogusch (
<number box="[263,322,1247,1271]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="2003.0">2003</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName authority="Schenck. We" authorityName="Schenck. We" box="[337,603,1247,1272]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="politum">
<emphasis box="[337,451,1248,1272]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">L. politum</emphasis>
Schenck. We
</taxonomicName>
also observed females of this species in association of 
<taxonomicName box="[1218,1359,1248,1272]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pauxillum">
<emphasis box="[1218,1359,1248,1272]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">L. pauxillum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctatissimum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">L. punctatissimum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, females of 
<taxonomicName box="[580,703,1285,1308]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="miniatus">
<emphasis box="[580,703,1285,1308]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">S. miniatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[865,1018,1285,1308]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginatus">
<emphasis box="[865,1018,1285,1308]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">S. marginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and other small 
<taxonomicName box="[1212,1330,1284,1308]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1212,1330,1284,1308]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Sphecodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, so study of the specialization in the field is difficult.
</paragraph>
